Top Men’s Seed Novak Djokovic of Serbia Reaches Semifinals at U.S. Open

-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 
2011-09-08T22:44:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-08/top-men-s-seed-novak-djokovic-of-serbia-reaches-semifinals-at-u-s-open.html
Top men’s seed Novak Djokovic
advanced to the semifinals of the U.S. Open when fellow Serb
Janko Tipsarevic, the 20th seed, retired in the fourth set of
their match.  Djokovic was leading 7-6 (7-2), 6-7 (3-7), 6-0, 3-0 when
Tipsarevic walked to the net to shake hands.  Djokovic next will play the winner of tonight’s
quarterfinal match between five-time champion  Roger Federer  of
 Switzerland  and Jo-Wilfried Tsonga, the 11th seed from  France .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  